title: Nike SB Zoom Dunk Elite Low
text: February 22, 2017 / nike sb Nike SB Zoom Dunk Elite Low The Nike SB Zoom Dunk Elite Low honors the past but points to the future of skating, reengineering the classic silhouette to be lighter and more flexible. The Dunk Elite features a larger Zoom Air bag in the midsole, to give riders maximum impact absorption, and a one-piece upper that eliminates seams in high-wear areas. The launch colorway for the new Dunk Elite Low is modeled off the original grey and blue SB Dunk sample that Sandy Bodecker (then the GM of Nike SB) first took around to skate shops in 2002. The shoe is available March 9 on nike.com and at select retailers.
